cessing."],"metadata":{"id":"DhEx8_jv2Pxe"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from datasets import load_dataset\n","\n","data_path = \"/content/drive/MyDrive/t5-data/merged_clean.jsonl\"\n","\n","dataset = load_dataset(\"json\", data_files=data_path)\n","\n","# Train-test split\n","dataset = dataset[\"train\"].train_test_split(test_size=0.1)\n","\n","print(dataset)"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"vPtTocKHlOZq","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776705071836,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":691,"user":{"displayName":"Sayan Dutta","userId":"05238912039351443293"}},"outputId":"c0950795-fba6-42eb-babb-e7452f6e1e67"},"execution_count":65,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["DatasetDict({\n","    train: Dataset({\n","        features: ['input', 'output', 'emotion', 'cause', 'paraphrase_style', 'difficulty', 'source', 'curriculum_rank'],\n","        num_rows: 215\n","    })\n","    test: Dataset({\n","        features: ['input', 'output', 'emotion', 'cause', 'paraphrase_style', 'difficulty', 'source', 'curriculum_rank'],\n","        num_rows: 24\n","    })\n","})\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Model Initialization (T5)\n","\n","In this step, we initialize the pre-trained T5 (Text-to-Text Transfer Transformer) model and its corresponding tokenizer. T5 is a versatile transformer model that treats all NLP tasks as a text-to-text problem, making it suitable for emotion-cause generation.\n","\n","We use the \"t5-small\" variant for faster training and lower computational cost, although larger variants like \"t5-base\" can provide better performance at the expense of speed and resources.\n","\n","The tokenizer is responsible for converting input text into token IDs, while the model generates the output sequence based on the given input."],"metadata":{"id":"rn6zyT_32bqx"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from transformers import T5Tokenizer, T5ForConditionalGeneration\n","\n","model_name = \"t5-small\"   # you can switch to \"t5-base\"\n","\n","tokenizer = T5Tokenizer.from_pretrained(model_name)\n","model = T5ForConditionalGeneration.from_pretrained(model_name)"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":49,"referenced_widgets":["1c5a136d187c4fd6b9d07fceda4f9221","35afb3e6f9a945ad943e43381ac09953","5af226605084416a8de336b3be87a140","f7ae3c44389e4a72bc7c35881c5f5a79","b503f27573d44cc49874e57f479683b6","22ba86a60b18486d8594532164e6336b","5d0867adeca147228d8df32c52e68365","2c26a5de798b48feba564547a3baaabf","35398a8669fa4a218d718ddffd7a3ea8","dcdaed50607f4a1ea5a90ab24907758e","ad8e77841cab4db58b682ebf8e564dfe"]},"id":"gsxre4nVmSiX","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776705074927,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":3074,"user":{"displayName":"Sayan Dutta","userId":"05238912039351443293"}},"outputId":"ee7df116-ba2a-4c85-db33-4742595ca617"},"execution_count":66,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["Loading weights:   0%|          | 0/131 [00:00<?, ?it/s]"],"application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json":{"version_major":2,"version_minor":0,"model_id":"1c5a136d187c4fd6b9d07fceda4f9221"}},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Data Preprocessing and Prompt Formatting\n","\n","In this step, we transform the raw dataset into a format suitable for training the T5 model. Since T5 follows a text-to-text paradigm, both inputs and outputs must be structured as natural language sequences.\n","\n","Each input sentence is converted into a task-specific prompt that clearly instructs the model to perform emotion-cause analysis. We also provide a fixed set of possible emotions to guide the model’s predictions.\n","\n","The target output is formatted as a structured string containing both the predicted emotion and its corresponding cause. After this, both inputs and targets are tokenized with appropriate padding and truncation to ensure uniform sequence lengths for efficient training.\n","\n","Finally, the processed inputs and labels are mapped across the entire dataset in a batched manner."],"metadata":{"id":"8dHrvX4v2kJu"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def preprocess(batch):\n","    inputs = [\n","        f\"\"\"Task: Emotion-Cause Analysis\n","Sentence: {inp}\n","Possible emotions: joy, sadness, anger, fear, surprise, disgust, guilt, embarrassment, disappointment\n","Predict emotion and cause.\"\"\"\n","        for inp in batch[\"input\"]\n","    ]\n","\n","    targets = [\n","        f\"Emotion: {emo} | Cause: {cause}\"\n","        for emo, cause in zip(batch[\"emotion\"], batch[\"cause\"])\n","    ]\n","\n","    model_inputs = tokenizer(\n","        inputs,\n","        max_length=128,\n","        truncation=True,\n","        padding=\"max_length\"\n","    )\n","\n","    labels = tokenizer(\n","        targets,\n","        max_length=64,\n","        truncation=True,\n","        padding=\"max_length\"\n","    )\n","\n","    model_inputs[\"labels\"] = labels[\"input_ids\"]\n","    return model_inputs\n","\n","\n","tokenized_dataset = dataset.map(preprocess, batched=True)"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":81,"referenced_widgets":["4d492db1c26a4794a122e08784d23c0e","81a80c6ce7d14fdb9372adb71a0a7ec2","9485d6eb5a0b47d1a34b1d22c261b10a","24af6890addc47248b0edc69abd40e77","90e52edae2e147499b974227d259b5a7","2b5287d6192c4b36b17133c5f653d514","3bd2273d89d546238ac0f1ebf8835d57","97eb0b12f56c488798e8310ccf488afe","146979b8e7824ac48b96f8737275c605","1cfd790fdbe0465e93d4b572e2bbc3d8","7f00e3bbef294f28a8a77501f7a029ce","79afbe5f2f424b97a57a23ad2b4c38c1","512d6d33c9dd4cdc89cef6cb6c4d22e3","96839698cc0b48c88649d65ed037b2c8","f909ffb644184560b685a44df25496d3","093ece9dd77f45c0a48cc7c4031a60d9","26ceabbd831548d9a561dd1e254f545e","78638aea775c489491b692312d07f46a","fa37e54b5d6246689393538fb773bc03","6b6a5d08b2e1405891fca873b3e492f2","fa09d58ff6e04478bf06c1f8d6ea6e11","534139f4e63b41c6bbafbfcc3469e4db"]},"id":"6tNPp6rJmneb","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776705075421,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":473,"user":{"displayName":"Sayan Dutta","userId":"05238912039351443293"}},"outputId":"4d6acb58-b912-439f-fa19-1dd9998f4354"},"execution_count":67,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["Map:   0%|          | 0/215 [00:00<?, ? examples/s]"],"application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json":{"version_major":2,"version_minor":0,"model_id":"4d492db1c26a4794a122e08784d23c0e"}},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["Map:   0%|          | 0/24 [00:00<?, ? examples/s]"],"application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json":{"version_major":2,"version_minor":0,"model_id":"79afbe5f2f424b97a57a23ad2b4c38c1"}},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Dataset Cleanup and Format Conversion\n","\n","After tokenization, the dataset still contains several original text and metadata columns that are no longer required for model training. These include fields such as raw input sentences, emotion labels, causes, and additional attributes like difficulty or source.\n","\n","In this step, we remove all unnecessary columns to keep only the tokenized inputs and labels. This helps reduce memory usage and ensures compatibility with the training pipeline.\n","\n","Finally, the dataset format is set to PyTorch tensors, allowing it to be directly used with the Hugging Face Trainer for efficient model training."],"metadata":{"id":"dyCNHEGW2sHJ"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["tokenized_dataset = tokenized_dataset.remove_columns(\n","    ['input', 'output', 'emotion', 'cause', 'paraphrase_style', 'difficulty', 'source', 'curriculum_rank']\n",")\n","tokenized_dataset.set_format(\"torch\")"],"metadata":{"id":"B11mdP_MnPdT","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776705075495,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":73,"user":{"displayName":"Sayan Dutta","userId":"05238912039351443293"}}},"execution_count":68,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Training Configuration and Hyperparameter Setup\n","\n","In this step, we define the training configuration using Hugging Face's Trainer API. The `TrainingArguments` class allows us to control key aspects of the training process, including batch size, number of epochs, learning rate, and checkpointing strategy.\n","\n","We set a moderate batch size to balance memory usage and training speed, and increase the number of epochs slightly to improve model learning. Evaluation and model saving are performed at the end of each epoch to monitor performance and retain the best checkpoints.\n","\n","Additional settings such as weight decay help in regularization, while mixed precision training (`fp16=True`) is enabled to accelerate computation and reduce GPU memory usage. Logging and reporting are configured to keep the training process clean and efficient."],"metadata":{"id":"2rXAk1ij20Ds"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from transformers import Trainer, TrainingArguments\n","\n","training_args = TrainingArguments(\n","    output_dir=\"/content/drive/MyDrive/t5_project/model\",\n","    per_device_train_batch_size=8,\n","    per_device_eval_batch_size=8,\n","    num_train_epochs=4,   # slightly increased\n","    eval_strategy=\"epoch\",\n","    save_strategy=\"epoch\",\n","    logging_dir=\"/content/drive/MyDrive/t5_project/logs\", # Corrected parameter name\n","    learning_rate=3e-4,\n","    weight_decay=0.01,\n","    save_total_limit=2,\n","    fp16=True,\n","    report_to=\"none\"   # disables wandb warnings\n",")"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"ZwAhuIZcnS-A","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776705075498,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":24,"user":{"displayName":"Sayan Dutta","userId":"05238912039351443293"}},"outputId":"30229b3d-b4c9-4a7c-8d02-56650e22f50d"},"execution_count":69,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stderr","text":["`logging_dir` is deprecated and will be removed in v5.2. Please set `TENSORBOARD_LOGGING_DIR` instead.\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Trainer Initialization\n","\n","In this step, we initialize the Hugging Face Trainer, which provides a high-level interface for model training and evaluation. It simplifies the training loop by handling batching, optimization, evaluation, and checkpointing internally.\n","\n","We pass the pre-trained T5 model, defined training arguments, and the tokenized training and evaluation datasets. The trainer will use these components to manage the full training pipeline efficiently."],"metadata":{"id":"yiDhbppt2-5O"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from transformers import Trainer\n","\n","trainer = Trainer(\n","    model=model,\n","    args=training_args,\n","    train_dataset=tokenized_dataset[\"train\"],\n","    eval_dataset=tokenized_dataset[\"test\"],\n",")"],"metadata":{"id":"IHN72RrQoTXp","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776705076357,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":860,"user":{"displayName":"Sayan Dutta","userId":"05238912039351443293"}}},"execution_count":70,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Model Training\n","\n","In this step, we begin training the model using the configured Trainer. The model learns to map input prompts to the desired emotion-cause outputs by minimizing the training loss over multiple epochs.\n","\n","During training, the model is periodically evaluated on the test dataset, and checkpoints are saved according to the defined strategy. This allows monitoring of performance and recovery of the best-performing model if needed."],"metadata":{"id":"x8QCFifo3Bc8"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["trainer.train()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":381,"referenced_widgets":["528a348fe3fb42758ddda030431399be","7dc6012abd5b4523b3f1aff780d4865a","5e178ae64caa4f229d1ebb5f845ce4af","82816ba2678a4a6392d0c6a080f676e4","fe276dd1ac724296ac7939c78eb779f9","b849b6ce3f08460f85b964f7d61660cc","79587c1e658147259f2b399cdbf8b37f","34993f4af964443481051dcca6795378","d26d09a8d6ab4017a64e134749359d55","8e66a4f324474da3a42510349d0a4318","f94552fb25a5403b9827ea0bfecbcaeb","d6f23269bd944cf6885fd35d5d34d930","08693f89b7c94032b3e841eef00f6350","f32e556f3142449395401dbf7f95688c","58ab36e523c94b79841d530c617dab03","3638f1c1c55b4ac689f9d72ea0cc6d7b","bbecb7eae22842a7aba8a2574ae49db1","1b3beae9abc94666a9207b35f7272aef","53cf7de61b7e4d39878f14918effc7b0","761d35db0cce474da256875b60d2b968","60664d267d0446d4bb99a07f41948f7c","beca81ad88464a6994e8da7580dd2c6a","7d26f83c7a554233ba6bf22b29f4cddd","94fc8358baaa4706be69f841a5758fcc","09d959b9d9dd48b99c36c7d3a4dcdebb","74591c569d554d65b112e0684f9cea8f","a8e92e76eaff4206bba94a6f6d02681d","349a2b67b6704855a692df16b4d054a3","c20a2759467043069c9866fee61eaf91","8cd2ee8ebe194d94b4980d4d07b9e53d","22fcf90c76fc43069ce0379d701f1f49","34380fc7885340058d676a8523cdc69d","876e7f20ef6b4c62b79727073e80a51a","d6e7d6544dd642d98535a82affbd86b9","11054508493e412fb36dd4624bad8050","f93b3e3cd48644f2a54ccedd199e4bc2","8e7695fb81bb4ebda44668a932cd8d06","3824636c799b4b7ead84780824c6fb66","3ec47ff43a6143faa67e116547d7fef5","4ec7c2c80d884b498d509e08cb2d909f","3ce8a82c0f864a3ab9dec7687b00af3f","b2ce16db5d3544fb853832aab632eb8f","7c6c7271fffd416fa1b5d2e3ddd6e67f","3f9434ec6adf47f18d9d200cbf221d6b"]},"id":"8rYl0AIfoWTO","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776705152258,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":75700,"user":{"displayName":"Sayan Dutta","userId":"05238912039351443293"}},"outputId":"999e4469-edba-4044-f16f-82369e57466c"},"execution_count":71,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<IPython.core.display.HTML object>"],"text/html":["\n","    <div>\n","      \n","      <progress value='108' max='108' style='width:300px; height:20px; vertical-align: middle;'></progress>\n","      [108/108 01:15, Epoch 4/4]\n","    </div>\n","    <table border=\"1\" class=\"dataframe\">\n","  <thead>\n"," <tr style=\"text-align: left;\">\n","      <th>Epoch</th>\n","      <th>Training Loss</th>\n","      <th>Validation Loss</th>\n","    </tr>\n","  </thead>\n","  <tbody>\n","    <tr>\n","      <td>1</td>\n","      <td>No log</td>\n","      <td>0.532391</td>\n","    </tr>\n","    <tr>\n","      <td>2</td>\n","      <td>No log</td>\n","      <td>0.353784</td>\n","    </tr>\n","    <tr>\n","      <td>3</td>\n","      <td>No log</td>\n","      <td>0.336245</td>\n","    </tr>\n","    <tr>\n","      <td>4</td>\n","      <td>No log</td>\n","      <td>0.329009</td>\n","    </tr>\n","  </tbody>\n","</table><p>"]},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["Writing model shards:   0%|          | 0/1 [00:00<?, ?it/s]"],"application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json":{"version_major":2,"version_minor":0,"model_id":"528a348fe3fb42758ddda030431399be"}},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["Writing model shards:   0%|          | 0/1 [00:00<?, ?it/s]"],"application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json":{"version_major":2,"version_minor":0,"model_id":"d6f23269bd944cf6885fd35d5d34d930"}},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["Writing model shards:   0%|          | 0/1 [00:00<?, ?it/s]"],"application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json":{"version_major":2,"version_minor":0,"model_id":"7d26f83c7a554233ba6bf22b29f4cddd"}},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["Writing model shards:   0%|          | 0/1 [00:00<?, ?it/s]"],"application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json":{"version_major":2,"version_minor":0,"model_id":"d6e7d6544dd642d98535a82affbd86b9"}},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["TrainOutput(global_step=108, training_loss=1.0203475245723017, metrics={'train_runtime': 75.6234, 'train_samples_per_second': 11.372, 'train_steps_per_second': 1.428, 'total_flos': 29098487316480.0, 'train_loss': 1.0203475245723017, 'epoch': 4.0})"]},"metadata":{},"execution_count":71}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Model Saving and Export\n","\n","After completing the training process, it is important to save the trained model and tokenizer for future use. This allows us to reuse the model for inference without retraining, and also enables sharing or deployment in other environments.\n","\n","The model and tokenizer are saved in a specified directory, preserving all learned parameters and configurations required for loading and prediction."],"metadata":{"id":"DPvt30Zu3Ir1"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["model.save_pretrained(\"/content/drive/MyDrive/t5_project/final_model\")\n","tokenizer.save_pretrained(\"/content/drive/MyDrive/t5_project/final_model\")"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":84,"referenced_widgets":["d62729722b6b45c3ae1e13df657f7dfe","70cac6bd0f06493c9cad5f1b00755d24","42f7bddb90e440f58d6973c1f38200cf","f5d27be4dee34caba9c754e679687193","8ad69c1720654a9b9b91347e145d33d1","49e05926604f4d37833257c7d868cf04","82386d7b326640f8bac413d6c7ecfe24","f540db08da514d87b96704ee536fd938","54d8641ec9a747fab1806979c772cde5","68706de675f3479f9ab1dbca7bf37cbb","091a5ab157214d22955497ff2c4870f3"]},"id":"aYc1jpsOojkK","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776705155628,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":3367,"user":{"displayName":"Sayan Dutta","userId":"05238912039351443293"}},"outputId":"eb0e12b7-3d17-4382-f3b6-0d7d4b11a6f2"},"execution_count":72,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["Writing model shards:   0%|          | 0/1 [00:00<?, ?it/s]"],"application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json":{"version_major":2,"version_minor":0,"model_id":"d62729722b6b45c3ae1e13df657f7dfe"}},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["('/content/drive/MyDrive/t5_project/final_model/tokenizer_config.json',\n"," '/content/drive/MyDrive/t5_project/final_model/tokenizer.json')"]},"metadata":{},"execution_count":72}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Model Loading for Inference\n","\n","In this step, we load the previously trained T5 model and tokenizer from the saved directory. This allows us to perform inference without retraining the model.\n","\n","The appropriate device (GPU or CPU) is automatically selected to ensure efficient computation. The model is then moved to the selected device and set to evaluation mode, which disables training-specific behaviors like dropout and ensures consistent predictions during inference."],"metadata":{"id":"ywJvsSXf3MSd"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from transformers import T5Tokenizer, T5ForConditionalGeneration\n","import torch\n","\n","model_path = \"/content/drive/MyDrive/t5_project/final_model\"\n","\n","tokenizer = T5Tokenizer.from_pretrained(model_path)\n","model = T5ForConditionalGeneration.from_pretrained(model_path)\n","\n","device = \"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\"\n","model.to(device)\n","model.eval()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":1000,"referenced_widgets":["eba781843f3d43bab5870688769b6ab1","04960c44ec8046fa8959a00b0425efaa","7455458e2b294eaeb6643efba71df3f9","40ebfd6848ab4b3fbd10455a947e6bbc","fff062de5d1d439b9bbc01fec9c1ba0d","0cb3cdae1e9645b3a062d26c540077f5","dcee4070aa514c1c868268a7ee794300","5005d608302d4b0b8ded75993d43c789","b804723a53c44f29b178d98988990ddf","4a2f07a8ac50496fab36db5b29642316","3df8a894aa5a45dd8d7adfe297969f86"]},"id":"gbi0EEpfpR2A","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776705299798,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":782,"user":{"displayName":"Sayan Dutta","userId":"05238912039351443293"}},"outputId":"240b77a9-56af-49c9-aaf4-e8a58525990c"},"execution_count":85,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["Loading weights:   0%|          | 0/131 [00:00<?, ?it/s]"],"application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json":{"version_major":2,"version_minor":0,"model_id":"eba781843f3d43bab5870688769b6ab1"}},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["T5ForConditionalGeneration(\n","  (shared): Embedding(32128, 512)\n","  (encoder): T5Stack(\n","    (embed_tokens): Embedding(32128, 512)\n","    (block): ModuleList(\n","      (0): T5Block(\n","        (layer): ModuleList(\n","          (0): T5LayerSelfAttention(\n","            (SelfAttention): T5Attention(\n","              (q): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (k): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (v): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (o): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (relative_attention_bias): Embedding(32, 8)\n","            )\n","            (layer_norm): T5LayerNorm()\n","            (dropout): Dropout(p=0.1, inplace=False)\n","          )\n","          (1): T5LayerFF(\n","            (DenseReluDense): T5DenseActDense(\n","              (wi): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=2048, bias=False)\n","              (wo): Linear(in_features=2048, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (dropout): Dropout(p=0.1, inplace=False)\n","              (act): ReLU()\n","            )\n","            (layer_norm): T5LayerNorm()\n","            (dropout): Dropout(p=0.1, inplace=False)\n","          )\n","        )\n","      )\n","      (1-5): 5 x T5Block(\n","        (layer): ModuleList(\n","          (0): T5LayerSelfAttention(\n","            (SelfAttention): T5Attention(\n","              (q): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (k): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (v): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (o): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","            )\n","            (layer_norm): T5LayerNorm()\n","            (dropout): Dropout(p=0.1, inplace=False)\n","          )\n","          (1): T5LayerFF(\n","            (DenseReluDense): T5DenseActDense(\n","              (wi): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=2048, bias=False)\n","              (wo): Linear(in_features=2048, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (dropout): Dropout(p=0.1, inplace=False)\n","              (act): ReLU()\n","            )\n","            (layer_norm): T5LayerNorm()\n","            (dropout): Dropout(p=0.1, inplace=False)\n","          )\n","        )\n","      )\n","    )\n","    (final_layer_norm): T5LayerNorm()\n","    (dropout): Dropout(p=0.1, inplace=False)\n","  )\n","  (decoder): T5Stack(\n","    (embed_tokens): Embedding(32128, 512)\n","    (block): ModuleList(\n","      (0): T5Block(\n","        (layer): ModuleList(\n","          (0): T5LayerSelfAttention(\n","            (SelfAttention): T5Attention(\n","              (q): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (k): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (v): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (o): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (relative_attention_bias): Embedding(32, 8)\n","            )\n","            (layer_norm): T5LayerNorm()\n","            (dropout): Dropout(p=0.1, inplace=False)\n","          )\n","          (1): T5LayerCrossAttention(\n","            (EncDecAttention): T5Attention(\n","              (q): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (k): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (v): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (o): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","            )\n","            (layer_norm): T5LayerNorm()\n","            (dropout): Dropout(p=0.1, inplace=False)\n","          )\n","          (2): T5LayerFF(\n","            (DenseReluDense): T5DenseActDense(\n","              (wi): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=2048, bias=False)\n","              (wo): Linear(in_features=2048, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (dropout): Dropout(p=0.1, inplace=False)\n","              (act): ReLU()\n","            )\n","            (layer_norm): T5LayerNorm()\n","            (dropout): Dropout(p=0.1, inplace=False)\n","          )\n","        )\n","      )\n","      (1-5): 5 x T5Block(\n","        (layer): ModuleList(\n","          (0): T5LayerSelfAttention(\n","            (SelfAttention): T5Attention(\n","              (q): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (k): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (v): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (o): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","            )\n","            (layer_norm): T5LayerNorm()\n","            (dropout): Dropout(p=0.1, inplace=False)\n","          )\n","          (1): T5LayerCrossAttention(\n","            (EncDecAttention): T5Attention(\n","              (q): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (k): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (v): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (o): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","            )\n","            (layer_norm): T5LayerNorm()\n","            (dropout): Dropout(p=0.1, inplace=False)\n","          )\n","          (2): T5LayerFF(\n","            (DenseReluDense): T5DenseActDense(\n","              (wi): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=2048, bias=False)\n","              (wo): Linear(in_features=2048, out_features=512, bias=False)\n","              (dropout): Dropout(p=0.1, inplace=False)\n","              (act): ReLU()\n","            )\n","            (layer_norm): T5LayerNorm()\n","            (dropout): Dropout(p=0.1, inplace=False)\n","          )\n","        )\n","      )\n","    )\n","    (final_layer_norm): T5LayerNorm()\n","    (dropout): Dropout(p=0.1, inplace=False)\n","  )\n","  (lm_head): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=32128, bias=False)\n",")"]},"metadata":{},"execution_count":85}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Inference Function: Emotion-Cause Prediction\n","\n","This function is designed to generate predictions from the trained T5 model for a given input sentence. It formats the input into a task-specific prompt, ensuring consistency with the format used during training.\n","\n","The input text is tokenized and passed to the model, which generates the output sequence using beam search for better quality predictions. The generated tokens are then decoded back into a human-readable string containing the predicted emotion and its corresponding cause.\n","\n","This function serves as the final interface for testing and demonstrating the model’s performance on new, unseen inputs."],"metadata":{"id":"inpkDNzx3Wcq"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def predict(text):\n","    input_text = f\"\"\"Task: Emotion-Cause Analysis\n","Sentence: {text}\n","Possible emotions: joy, sadness, anger, fear, surprise, disgust, guilt, embarrassment, disappointment\n","Predict emotion and cause.\"\"\"\n","\n","    inputs = tokenizer(input_text, return_tensors=\"pt\", truncation=True).to(device)\n","\n","    outputs = model.generate(\n","        **inputs,\n","        max_length=50,\n","        num_beams=4,\n","        early_stopping=True\n","    )\n","\n","    return tokenizer.decode(outputs[0], skip_special_tokens=True)"],"metadata":{"id":"EXqcsrR8pUhY","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776705302243,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":25,"user":{"displayName":"Sayan Dutta","userId":"05238912039351443293"}}},"execution_count":86,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Example Predictions and Model Evaluation\n","\n","In this step, we test the trained model on a set of sample sentences to evaluate its ability to correctly identify emotions and their underlying causes.\n","\n","These examples cover a variety of real-life scenarios, allowing us to observe how well the model generalizes to unseen inputs. The outputs provide qualitative insight into the model’s performance and coherence in generating emotion-cause pairs."],"metadata":{"id":"-DfXGEv13j0e"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["print(predict(\"They gave promotion to someone else\"))\n","print(predict(\"I lost my wallet yesterday\"))\n","print(predict(\"My friend surprised me on my birthday\"))\n","print(predict(\"He ignored my messages all day\"))\n","print(predict(\"I got a scholership\"))"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"IOTMbMtwpXMC","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776705328675,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":1168,"user":{"displayName":"Sayan Dutta","userId":"05238912039351443293"}},"outputId":"18d68ad5-68c5-46b2-ce7b-e8d878c71776"},"execution_count":88,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Emotion: pride | Cause: being promoted to someone else\n","Emotion: sadness | Cause: losing a wallet\n","Emotion: surprise | Cause: surprise on a birthday\n","Emotion: anger | Cause: being ignored\n","Emotion: sadness | Cause: a scholership\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def test_examples():\n","    samples = dataset[\"test\"].select(range(5))\n","\n","    for s in samples:\n","        print(\"INPUT :\", s[\"input\"])\n","        print(\"TRUE  :\", f\"Emotion: {s['emotion']} | Cause: {s['cause']}\")\n","        print(\"PRED  :\", predict(s[\"input\"]))\n","        print(\"-\"*60)\n","\n","test_examples()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"AfXLsD98pfkL","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776705344934,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":1167,"user":{"displayName":"Sayan Dutta","userId":"05238912039351443293"}},"outputId":"0da2630a-f6b7-4bad-8497-6107c787e225"},"execution_count":89,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["INPUT : Analyze emotion and cause: It happened that i mentored someone and they got the job\n","TRUE  : Emotion: pride | Cause: mentee getting the job\n","PRED  : Emotion: disappointment | Cause: mentoring someone\n","------------------------------------------------------------\n","INPUT : Analyze emotion and cause: Looking back, the results were far below what i expected\n","TRUE  : Emotion: disappointment | Cause: results falling below expectations\n","PRED  : Emotion: disappointment | Cause: results far below what i expected\n","------------------------------------------------------------\n","INPUT : Analyze emotion and cause: The truth is, i have explained it in three different ways and they still do not understand\n","TRUE  : Emotion: frustration | Cause: communication breakdown after repeated effort\n","PRED  : Emotion: anger | Cause: misunderstanding in three ways\n","------------------------------------------------------------\n","INPUT : Analyze emotion and cause: The project was rejected and I was told to redo it from scratch. I am not over it yet.\n","TRUE  : Emotion: frustration | Cause: project rejection and being told to redo from scratch\n","PRED  : Emotion: disappointment | Cause: rejection of a project\n","------------------------------------------------------------\n","INPUT : Analyze emotion and cause: I just realized i passed a difficult exam\n","TRUE  : Emotion: joy | Cause: passing a difficult exam\n","PRED  : Emotion: disappointment | Cause: passing a difficult exam\n","------------------------------------------------------------\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import re\n","\n","def extract_emotion(text):\n","    match = re.search(r\"Emotion:\\s*(\\w+)\", text)\n","    return match.group(1).lower() if match else \"unknown\"\n","\n","def compute_accuracy():\n","    correct = 0\n","    total = 0\n","\n","    for sample in dataset[\"test\"]:\n","        true_emotion = sample[\"emotion\"].lower()\n","        pred_output = predict(sample[\"input\"])\n","        pred_emotion = extract_emotion(pred_output)\n","\n","        if pred_emotion == true_emotion:\n","            correct += 1\n","\n","        total += 1\n","\n","    accuracy = correct / total\n","    print(f\"Emotion Accuracy: {accuracy:.2f} ({correct}/{total})\")\n","\n","compute_accuracy()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"RN-nmKeHpyRL","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776705175258,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":8360,"user":{"displayName":"Sayan Dutta","userId":"05238912039351443293"}},"outputId":"12b071ea-c78f-468f-e557-ee97ee20538a"},"execution_count":77,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Emotion Accuracy: 0.25 (6/24)\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["SIMILAR = {\n","    \"anger\": [\"frustration\"],\n","    \"sadness\": [\"guilt\", \"disappointment\"],\n","    \"disappointment\": [\"sadness\"],\n","    \"guilt\": [\"sadness\"],\n","}\n","\n","def is_match(true, pred):\n","    if true == pred:\n","        return True\n","    if true in SIMILAR and pred in SIMILAR[true]:\n","        return True\n","    return False\n","\n","def compute_relaxed_accuracy():\n","    correct = 0\n","    total = 0\n","\n","    for sample in dataset[\"test\"]:\n","        true_emotion = sample[\"emotion\"].lower()\n","        pred_output = predict(sample[\"input\"])\n","        pred_emotion = extract_emotion(pred_output)\n","\n","        if is_match(true_emotion, pred_emotion):\n","            correct += 1\n","\n","        total += 1\n","\n","    accuracy = correct / total\n","    print(f\"Relaxed Accuracy: {accuracy:.2f} ({correct}/{total})\")\n","\n","compute_relaxed_accuracy()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"8ODwa-qnp5Es","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776705428511,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":4447,"user":{"displayName":"Sayan Dutta","userId":"05238912039351443293"}},"outputId":"2fc71bea-01a7-43e9-b363-4e253e51f70f"},"execution_count":90,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Relaxed Accuracy: 0.25 (6/24)\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def simple_cause_score(true, pred):\n","    true_words = set(true.lower().split())\n","    pred_words = set(pred.lower().split())\n","\n","    overlap = len(true_words & pred_words)\n","    return overlap / len(true_words) if true_words else 0\n","simple_cause_score(\"sadness\", \"guilt\")"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"v4wSUJPAp-YZ","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776705181879,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":28,"user":{"displayName":"Sayan Dutta","userId":"05238912039351443293"}},"outputId":"fc07597e-1536-4ba8-8dd9-2bd896e8bf55"},"execution_count":79,"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["0.0"]},"metadata":{},"execution_count":79}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def show_errors():\n","    for sample in dataset[\"test\"]:\n","        true_emotion = sample[\"emotion\"].lower()\n","        pred_output = predict(sample[\"input\"])\n","        pred_emotion = extract_emotion(pred_output)\n","\n","        if true_emotion != pred_emotion:\n","            print(\"INPUT:\", sample[\"input\"])\n","            print(\"TRUE:\", true_emotion)\n","            print(\"PRED:\", pred_emotion)\n","            print(\"-\"*40)\n","\n","show_errors()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"uEjzSp0VqPuR","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776705196014,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":14133,"user":{"displayName":"Sayan Dutta","userId":"05238912039351443293"}},"outputId":"45cd200c-25eb-47dc-99dd-554b1115da36"},"execution_count":80,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["INPUT: Analyze emotion and cause: It happened that i mentored someone and they got the job\n","TRUE: pride\n","PRED: disappointment\n","----------------------------------------\n","INPUT: Analyze emotion and cause: The truth is, i have explained it in three different ways and they still do not understand\n","TRUE: frustration\n","PRED: anger\n","----------------------------------------\n","INPUT: Analyze emotion and cause: The project was rejected and I was told to redo it from scratch. I am not over it yet.\n","TRUE: frustration\n","PRED: disappointment\n","----------------------------------------\n","INPUT: Analyze emotion and cause: I just realized i passed a difficult exam\n","TRUE: joy\n","PRED: disappointment\n","----------------------------------------\n","INPUT: Analyze emotion and cause: The project was rejected and I was told to redo it from scratch — still feeling it\n","TRUE: frustration\n","PRED: disappointment\n","----------------------------------------\n","INPUT: Analyze emotion and cause: Reflecting on it now — i helped my family through a hard time\n","TRUE: pride\n","PRED: sadness\n","----------------------------------------\n","INPUT: Analyze emotion and cause: Reflecting on it now — i heard strange noises at night\n","TRUE: fear\n","PRED: sadness\n","----------------------------------------\n","INPUT: Analyze emotion and cause: Recently, my student topped the class\n","TRUE: pride\n","PRED: disappointment\n","----------------------------------------\n","INPUT: Analyze emotion and cause: I keep thinking about how my voice cracked while presenting\n","TRUE: embarrassment\n","PRED: sadness\n","----------------------------------------\n","INPUT: Analyze emotion and cause: Recently, i completed my project successfully\n","TRUE: joy\n","PRED: disappointment\n","----------------------------------------\n","INPUT: Analyze emotion and cause: I ignored someone who needed help and it affected me deeply\n","TRUE: guilt\n","PRED: frustration\n","----------------------------------------\n","INPUT: Analyze emotion and cause: Honestly, nobody forced me, but i still feel like i had no choice\n","TRUE: frustration\n","PRED: anger\n","----------------------------------------\n","INPUT: Analyze emotion and cause: bruh they literally took credit for my thing\n","TRUE: anger\n","PRED: sadness\n","----------------------------------------\n","INPUT: Analyze emotion and cause: Honestly, i have an exam tomorrow\n","TRUE: fear\n","PRED: disappointment\n","----------------------------------------\n","INPUT: Analyze emotion and cause: I lost my job and my landlord raised the rent the next morning — still feeling it\n","TRUE: fear\n","PRED: frustration\n","----------------------------------------\n","INPUT: Analyze emotion and cause: It happened that i sent a personal message to the wrong group chat\n","TRUE: embarrassment\n","PRED: sadness\n","----------------------------------------\n","INPUT: Analyze emotion and cause: i overcame something i once feared\n","TRUE: pride\n","PRED: sadness\n","----------------------------------------\n","INPUT: Analyze emotion and cause: It wasn't a big deal, but I keep thinking about what I said — still feeling it\n","TRUE: guilt\n","PRED: anger\n","----------------------------------------\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, ConfusionMatrixDisplay\n","import re\n","\n","# Extract emotion\n","def extract_emotion(text):\n","    match = re.search(r\"Emotion:\\s*(\\w+)\", text)\n","    return match.group(1).lower() if match else \"unknown\"\n","\n","# Collect predictions\n","y_true = []\n","y_pred = []\n","\n","for sample in dataset[\"test\"]:\n","    true_emotion = sample[\"emotion\"].lower()\n","    pred_output = predict(sample[\"input\"])\n","    pred_emotion = extract_emotion(pred_output)\n","\n","    y_true.append(true_emotion)\n","    y_pred.append(pred_emotion)\n","\n","# Get unique labels\n","labels = sorted(list(set(y_true + y_pred)))\n","\n","# Confusion matrix\n","cm = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred, labels=labels)\n","\n","# Plot\n","plt.figure()\n","disp = ConfusionMatrixDisplay(confusion_matrix=cm, display_labels=labels)\n","disp.plot()\n","plt.title(\"Confusion Matrix - Emotion Classification\")\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"id":"8BO5pAqBqGye","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776705210812,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":14751,"user":{"displayName":"Sayan Dutta","userId":"05238912039351443293"}},"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":489},"outputId":"d3001de3-7e82-4bc8-845a-4e56b32bfade"},"execution_count":81,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 0 Axes>"]},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 2 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# Extract logs\n","logs = trainer.state.log_history\n","\n","train_loss = []\n","eval_loss = []\n","epochs = []\n","\n","for log in logs:\n","    if \"loss\" in log:\n","        train_loss.append(log[\"loss\"])\n","    if \"eval_loss\" in log:\n","        eval_loss.append(log[\"eval_loss\"])\n","        epochs.append(log[\"epoch\"])\n","\n","# Plot\n","plt.figure()\n","plt.plot(range(len(train_loss)), train_loss, label=\"Train Loss\")\n","plt.plot(range(len(eval_loss)), eval_loss, label=\"Eval Loss\")\n","\n","plt.xlabel(\"Steps / Epochs\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Loss\")\n","plt.title(\"Training vs Evaluation Loss\")\n","plt.legend()\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":472},"id":"5PDr_bvgz1Sf","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776705211017,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":192,"user":{"displayName":"Sayan Dutta","userId":"05238912039351443293"}},"outputId":"2afc6865-11f7-4eb3-a0ce-304e457630d7"},"execution_count":82,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["accuracies = [0.54, 0.62]  # your values\n","labels = [\"Strict Accuracy\", \"Relaxed Accuracy\"]\n","\n","plt.figure()\n","plt.bar(labels, accuracies)\n","plt.ylim(0, 1)\n","plt.ylabel(\"Accuracy\")\n","plt.title(\"Model Performance\")\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":452},"id":"u8crNAKiz5aT","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776705211090,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":70,"user":{"displayName":"Sayan Dutta","userId":"05238912039351443293"}},"outputId":"b4f2ec22-0ad9-4e5b-8b99-b1bd67dbd34a"},"execution_count":83,"outputs":[{"output_type":"dis